 Ice Cream Museum Food, food, food… we all love food. Food permeates into our culture and way of life. Aside from the usual communication with food, which begins with the eyes, nose, mouth and stomach, it is textualised into art to the point foods are housed as art forms in museums. Food museums are institutions that showcase the history, culture, and significance of food and drink and the science of taste and nutrition. They often feature interactive exhibits, historical artefacts and educational programmes that explore the ways in which food has shaped societies and cultures throughout history. These museums focus on a certain food or variety of food to delve into its respective world. Each place showcases the history of the item and interesting facts regarding the food of choice. However, some spotlight just one good and others showcase a range of foods. If you are a foodie, here are top food museums around the world. Ice Cream Museum Home to the Museum of Ice Cream is San Francisco. The popular dessert is the focus of the museum, which features a number of entertaining exhibitions. Visitors are treated to viewing vibrant displays of the ice cream industry’s scrumptious history. All five of your senses are intended to be pampered at the Museum of Ice Cream. With the experiments of recipes featuring peanut butter, tropical mango, and a few more beloved tastes, there are even some new varieties of ice cream to taste. <br />Belgian-city-museum-of-the-Frietmuseum Frietmuseum
In the Belgian city of Bruges, there is a museum called the Frietmuseum that celebrates French fries. The museum delves further into one of many foodies’ favourite appetisers by examining several historical topics regarding fries. The first floor will feature exhibitions that will cover three floors and tell the story of frites. On the second floor, exhibitions of artwork, chip-producing equipment, and other items reveal the excitement that goes into making fries. On the ground floor below is a café that serves specialty fries in various shapes.
