Potato Museum
Still on fries Idaho is recognised for its potatoes, it is understandable why the Potato Museum is one of the best culinary museums in the world. Situated in​ Blackfoot, Idaho, it offers the finest experience for everyone who is captivated by potatoes. The museum historically details the potato and its significance for the state of Idaho throughout the tour of the Potato Museum. The community and food are celebrated through exhibits and stunning murals. The cost of entrance to the Potato Museum is only $6, and it is even less expensive for children. Gingerbread man
The Gingerbread man comes alive in the Czech Republic located in Prague. Even though it is frequently seen as being too small to qualify as a museum, going there is nonetheless enjoyable. Some of the most exquisite gingerbread houses and other cookie patterns ever created can be found there. Given how outstanding majority of the graphics are, this is regarded as an artistic presentation. In addition to being delectable, gingerbread cookies may inspire even the most imaginative people to think of inventive ways to use them. Before you leave the Gingerbread Museum, you can purchase some delectable goodies. <br />Hussel-Chocolat-Shop-Schokoladenmusem-Koeln Chocolate Museum​
Located in Cologne, Germany this museum is dedicated to the history of chocolate, and features exhibits on the origins of chocolate, the process of making chocolate, and the cultural significance of chocolate. Beer Museum​
This museum is in Brussels, Belgium and explores the history of beer and its cultural significance. It features exhibits on the history of beer-making, as well as interactive displays that allow visitors to experience the process of making beer. hyogo-hakutsuru-sake-brewery-museum. Sake Museum​
Located in Tokyo, Japan This museum explores the history of sake and its cultural significance. It features exhibits on the history of sake-making, as well as interactive displays that allow visitors to experience the process of making sake. Musee_schaerbeekois_biere-Schaerbeek-beer-museum Museum of Food and Drink​
This particular museum is in Paris, which explores the history and culture of French cuisine through interactive exhibits, workshops, and events. Other Museum of Food and Drink
London, which features interactive exhibits and hands-on activities that explore the history of food and drink in the UK. In Tokyo, the Museum of Food and Drink showcases the history and culture of Japanese cuisine through interactive exhibits, workshops and events. In Berlin, which explores the history and culture of German cuisine through interactive exhibits, workshops, and events. 